In article <33oclv$5jh@prime.mdata.fi> kiril@mits.mdata.fi (Kiril Kesarev) writes:
:	I have read somewhere that the Miller-Rabin primality test can be
:made to perform tests in polynomial time, by using only certain bases.
:Can someone, please, give more information about this primality test.
:
If the size of the primes is bounded to less than 25 x 10^9,  *OR* the
GRH is true, then it does give a deterministic P-time algorithm. 

Otherwise, to the best of my knowledge, the claim is false.

While the GRH is believed to be true, a proof is lacking.
-- 
Bob Silverman
